reviewText: This was filmed on January 18, 1978. It has a running time of approximately 52 minutes. Overall, I was a little disappointed, I was expecting a better show. It's good, but it comes across as a little too "mellow" for me.The line-up:Merle Haggard - guitar, fiddle, vocalsBonnie Owens (Merle's Ex)- tamborime, backing vocalsRonnie Reno - guitarBiff Adam - drumsPaul Anastasio - fiddleWayne Durham - bassNorman Hamlet - steel guitarDon Markham - saxaphone, trumpetRoy Nichols - guitarGordon Terry - fiddleMark Yeary - pianoThe songs:1.Working Man Can't Get Nowhere Today2.Silver Wings (A Merle Haggard Classic)3.Ramblin' Fever4.Lonesome Fugitive5.Sing Me Back Home (Another Merle Haggard Classic)6.Orange Blossom Special7.Old Fashioned Love8.Long Black Limousine9.Cherokee Maiden10.San Antonio Rose (a Bob Wills song)11.Misery12.Farmer's Daughter13.Brain Cloudy Blues14.Workin' Man Blues (Another Merle Haggard Classic)Thanks!!!!
summary: A Good Concert by Merle Haggard & His Huge Backing Band

reviewText: This is Merle as he should always be remembered.A hundred years from now when someone asks "What was Merle Haggard like?". This is the document that should be produced to prove what so many in this lifetime know. Merle is an American Treasure.Wonderfully recorded here in Austin TX in 1985. This DVD drips with sentimentality and still delivers a punch.If you only own a single Merle DVD make it this one.The band is spectacular and Merle hits on all cylinders.
